    {
        "client_msg_id": "50901d8c-2432-43ab-a3f9-8151fb8d2c81",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "Yeah, that's something we ran into with Crosscut and didn't really engage with. The freedom to draw \"whatever\" at the concrete level is really pleasing; being able to manipulate the \"whatever\" using a dynamic system is appealing. But having vector math be the _only_ way to do that dynamic manipulation is such a narrow channel through which to work \u2014 it's very unlikely to match the character of the \"whatever\" you drew.\n\nI'd like to lean away from geometric representation entirely. That means no vector math \u2014 probably no math at all. I want to see what _that_ dynamic / programming system might look like.",
